<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>debezium event decoder — paste JSON, see diffs &amp; SQL</title>
    <meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" name="viewport" />
    <meta
      content="paste Debezium JSON events (or DLQ records), see op/source, before/after diff, headers &amp; errors, and a ready-to-tweak MERGE/UPSERT template. all local."
      name="description"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/pages/debezium-decoder.css">
    <link
      href="https://letstalkcdc.nfshost.com/debezium-decoder.html"
      rel="canonical"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <a class="skip-link" href="#main">Skip to content</a>
    <header>
      <a href="/everything-else/">← extras</a>
      <h1>debezium event decoder</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        paste JSON events from Kafka (Debezium or Connect DLQ). we’ll detect
        op/source, show a before/after diff, reveal headers &amp; errors, and
        generate a base MERGE/UPSERT. everything runs locally in your browser.
      </p>
    </header>
    <main class="wrap" id="top">
      <section class="panel">
        <h2>1) paste event(s)</h2>
        <p class="muted small">
          paste lines from <code>kafka-console-consumer</code> (schema-less
          JSON) or Connect DLQ records. multiple lines ok; non-JSON lines are
          ignored.
        </p>
        <textarea
          id="inp"
          placeholder='{"before":null,"after":{"id":1,"email":"a@example.com"},"op":"c","source":{"db":"postgres","schema":"app","table":"customer"},"ts_ms":1724700000000}'
          spellcheck="false"
        ></textarea>
        <div class="row">
          <button class="btn" id="btnSample">try sample</button>
          <input
            accept=".json,.txt"
            class="btn"
            id="file"
            title="open .json/.txt file"
            type="file"
          />
          <label class="small"
            ><input id="flatten" type="checkbox" /> flatten nested fields
            (dot-notation)</label
          >
          <span class="muted small">privacy: nothing leaves this page.</span>
        </div>
        <h2 style="margin-top: 1rem">2) keys &amp; sink</h2>
        <div class="row">
          <label class="small">key columns:</label>
          <input class="btn" id="keys" style="min-width: 220px" value="id" />
          <button class="btn" id="btnSuggest" title="suggest keys from data">
            suggest
          </button>
          <span class="small muted"
            >comma-separate multi-column keys
            (<code>acct_id,order_id</code>).</span
          >
        </div>
        <div aria-label="sink" class="tabs" role="tablist">
          <button class="active" data-sink="postgres" role="tab">
            postgres
          </button>
          <button data-sink="snowflake" role="tab">snowflake</button>
          <button data-sink="bigquery" role="tab">bigquery</button>
          <button data-sink="delta" role="tab">databricks delta</button>
          <button data-sink="mysql" role="tab">mysql</button>
          <button data-sink="redshift" role="tab">redshift</button>
        </div>
        <button class="btn copy" id="copySql">copy SQL</button>
        <pre><code id="sql">-- paste an event to generate a MERGE/UPSERT template…</code></pre>
        <div class="foot">
          we infer columns from your last event’s <code>after</code> (or
          <code>before</code> for deletes). adjust names as needed.
        </div>
        <div class="hint" id="keyHint" style="display: none"></div>
      </section>
      <section class="panel">
        <h2>decoded</h2>
        <div class="grid" id="results"></div>
</section>
</main>
    <script type="module" src="/assets/js/app.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
